 | doi = 10.1103/PhysRevB.78.224306
|bibcode = 2008PhRvB..78v4306B |arxiv = 0807.2458 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news.cornell.edu/stories/2009/04/frozen-helium-4-may-be-unusual-superglass|title=Press release: Supersolid or superglass? Cornell researchers study a strange state of matter in helium - Cornell Chronicle|publisher=|access-date=2020-10-30|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112014241/https://news.cornell.edu/stories/2009/04/frozen-helium-4-may-be-unusual-superglass|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|arxiv=1111.5956|title=Mean field theory of superglasses|journal=Physical Review B|volume=85|issue=10|pages=104205|last1=Yu|first1=Xiaoquan|last2=Mueller|first2=Markus|year=2011|doi=10.1103/PhysRevB.85.104205|bibcode=2012PhRvB..85j4205Y}}</ref>

